You smash what remains of the window to pieces and clamber through, the song's urgent beauty distracting you from any cuts.
-You enter a small hidden courtyard. It appears to have been blocked off from the rest of the monastery sometime after its construction.
*[Look around]

You get down onto your haunches and scrabble around in the dirt and grass. 

-(inscription){You find small beads inscribed with spirals, candle stumps, and fragments of wood covered in faded carvings. <i>Something</i> was once worshipped here. |What else?}

*[Inspect the beads] You hold one of the beads up to your eye. They look to be made from bone. They appear slightly ovular in shape and each is tipped with a yellow opal, the colour of which runs through the etched spirals like veins. ->inscription  //fred: I find the last sentence unclear to imagine for some reason , can you think of another way to describe what you mean? 
