*[Gather the wood together] You manage to connect some of the scraps of wood into the semblance of a whole text - it's a prayer of some kind.

<i>...and so our fecund lord, who bounds through the gloaming... make haste to greet your piteous subjects...we from whom you spring eternal...Lapinite songs uplift you...swiftly dash through warren and briar, bringing with your blessing...anoint our Lagomane as your chosen...use the vessel...bring forth your divine music...keen through the sepulchre...<i>

-Your nose twitches as you read the fragments of an ancient call to an ancient god. Something is buried here. 

*[BURROW]

-You scratch-scratch-scratch at the hard-packed earth. You don't know what you're looking for, but you know it's here. Just as you begin to lose faith, your dirt-caked hands reveal something.

*[UNEARTH]

A figurine of a Hare, carved in the same material as the beads, with yellow opals for eyes. This is what was making the song. 

-You can <b>smell</b> it, and <b>hear</b> it, and <b>taste</b> it. The song of things <b>growing</b>, of things <b>multiplying</b>, of things <b>becoming greater</b> than they are. The song of <b>creeping overgrowth</b> and <b>glut</b> and <b>rot</b>. It sings to you now of <b>change</b>, an <b>incredible change</b>. One already partly underway. 

*[<b>ACCEPT THE SONG</b>]->transformation
*[Reject the song] The hare figurine crumbles away to ash in your hands - leaving only its opal eyes. The bite on your hand throbs sharply. You have a feeling it will never fully heal. 

You should leave this place before something worse happens ->enter_mon

==transformation

The Bone-Hare's eyes glow yellow and the timpanic pounding, the cacophany of rush and dew and fervor, coalesces into a single keening note. Beginning in the wound on your hand, it reverberates through your very being. 
*[<b>CHANGE</b>]
<i>Wound closing - flesh tearing - muscle engorging - hair spreading - tooth elongating - nail sharpening - ear stretching - stature building - divine encapsulating

<i>frog - viper - cicada - ant - butterfly  - alate - larvae - egg - embryo - spawn - paturate</i>

<i>shed - molt - cocoon - pupate - metamorphise -</i> 
**[EMERGE] 

- I <b>am</b> now. I <b>smell</b> now I <b>hear</b> now. Out - out - out - time to <b>run</b>, time to <b>flee</b>. I once was lost. I once was other. I can <b>grow</b> more - must grow more. 

**[ESCAPE]
I <b>hop-hop-leap</b> over the stone walls. I land near a chewing creature. A  malevolent creature. I did not see it before for what it truly was. Like my Lord, but older. Weaker. 
***[RUIN] I <b>twitch-twitch-twitch</b> my nose and a great groaning I hear and I can feel the <b>growth</b> that overtakes the old-stone building. The Laughing Nightmare looks at me in surprise and makes to laugh again, but too late for he is already <b>flesh-become-rotten-become-skin-become-bone</b>. 
***[RUN] <b>Where to-where to- where to?</b>

---I soar into the sky, over <b>rush-raging</b> stream and <b>thump-thump-thump</b> down into the glorious overgrowth. What a fool I was to fear it. Next-

****[TUNNEL] I scurry-rush through the undergrowth. What <b>strength</b> I have now, what skill. I am the greatest conjoining of my form and my lord; enough of me is still capable of what the <b>beast</b> is not.  

----I emerge at a ruined place. Some growth, not much. And that woman again. The vexing-hexing woman who tormented-toyed with me so when I desired leave. I would not wish such a thing now.

*****[TALK]I <b>thump-land</b> on her platform and she emerges to see my glorious state. Her eyes widen. <p>"You shouldn't have done that. Each to their own, I suppose. I assume you won't be needing that train anymore then."</p> She laughs wanly. I tell her of my <b>purpose</b>. She knows there is nothing she can do. Perhaps she will leave. She will leave.
*****[TERRORISE] I beat-beat-beat upon the ground and watch as the building becomes <b>consumed</b> by the creeping earth. She emerges from her crumbling den and stares at me.
I tell her that she should have kept us away better. Her claim on this land is worthless now. I cannot kill her, unnatural entity, bridge to choking-smog barren land.
 The <b>pulse-lurch</b> of the <b>hunt</b> must have her never still. I can make it so.

----- The sun begins to set. I must make a den. Make plans. ->rabbit_ending 

