==stay_end

The stationmaster stands behind you.

"One last farewell?"

You explain to her that, for some reason, you don't want to leave.

"I'll be flattered and believe that to be about my company." Her face hides an emotion that you don't think you recognise.

*You wonder if it is.

Whatever the case - be it the serenity of {enter_mon: the monastery| the woods}, the cosiness of the stationhouse, or just the escape from a life outside you can't remember, you know that you wish to stay. For now, at least.

"Luckily for you, I have a spare room. I'll get you settled in and we can wake up bright and early tomorrow with pancakes. I have some jobs that you can do while you're with me."

The stationmaster takes you by the shoulders and leads you away from the edge of the platform as the train pulls away into the setting sun.

